  "object_type": "TABLE",
  "description": "BEN_LER_CHG_PTIP_ENRT_F identifies the impact of a life event reason on the election changes a person may or may not make to plans of a specified plan type in a program.  Each record specifies whether the parameters defined apply to persons who are currently participating in plans of the specified plan types in the program or if, as a result of the life event, they are newly eligible to enroll.  For example,  a person is newly eligible to enroll in  medical coverage in the Acme Benefits Program because of a change of residence postal code life event.",
